text: <@U01NZHCBBQB> So looks like you have two separate bodies in a single STL part file. I would recommend saving them individually and upload them one by one to the online slicer (this is to prevent the case where the parts are slightly misaligned in the assembly file and causing issues on the first layer). Since your pieces will have a small contact area on the printed, I would recommend selecting "brim" under the adhesion method. The other settings I would recommend is "225deg/60deg, <http://0.mm|0.20mm> layer height". A <http://0.mm|0>.05mm layer height is probably not necessary for the geometry, and printing it in 0.2mm will save the print time by order of magnitude with minimal change to the quality
